userStories.notes:
File: platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/PluginCard.tsx

Current state: TabStateHint (lines 25-41) is rendered INSIDE Accordion.Content (line 176), which is only visible when the card is expanded. The collapsed header (AccordionPrimitive.Trigger, lines 112-153) only shows the icon, display name, badges, chevron, and toggle.

Approach: Move the status hint INTO the trigger header, displayed as a secondary line under the plugin name. The trigger already has a div wrapping the display name text (lines 132-151). Add the hint as a second line inside that div.

Change the name container from:
```tsx
<div className="font-head text-foreground min-w-0 flex-1 truncate text-sm">
  {plugin.displayName}
  {/* badges */}
</div>
```

To a flex column:
```tsx
<div className="min-w-0 flex-1">
  <div className="font-head text-foreground flex items-center gap-1.5 truncate text-sm">
    {plugin.displayName}
    {/* badges */}
  </div>
  {plugin.tabState !== 'ready' && (
    <div className={`truncate text-[10px] leading-tight ${
      plugin.tabState === 'closed' ? 'text-destructive' : 'text-muted-foreground'
    }`}>
      {plugin.tabState === 'closed'
        ? (domain ? `Open ${domain}` : 'No tab open')
        : 'Waiting…'}
    </div>
  )}
</div>
```

Then remove the TabStateHint component definition (lines 25-41) and its usage at line 176. Also remove the extractDomain import if it was only used by TabStateHint — but we still need it for the inline hint, so keep it but use it in the new location.

Update Storybook stories to show the new inline hints in collapsed state.
